04 8:1 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 8:2 Speak to Aaron and say to him: When you set up the lamps, the seven lamps shall give light in front of the lampstand.
04 8:3 Aaron did so; he set up its lamps to give light in front of the lampstand, as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04 8:4 Now this was how the lampstand was made, out of hammered work of gold. From its base to its flowers, it was hammered work; according to the pattern that the LORD had shown Moses, so he made the lampstand.
04 8:5 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 8:6 Take the Levites from among the Israelites and cleanse them.
04 8:7 Thus you shall do to them, to cleanse them: sprinkle the water of purification on them, have them shave their whole body with a razor and wash their clothes, and so cleanse themselves.
04 8:8 Then let them take a young bull and its grain offering of choice flour mixed with oil, and you shall take another young bull for a sin offering.
04 8:9 You shall bring the Levites before the tent of meeting, and assemble the whole congregation of the Israelites.
04 8:10 When you bring the Levites before the LORD, the Israelites shall lay their hands on the Levites,
04 8:11 and Aaron shall present the Levites before the LORD as an elevation offering from the Israelites, that they may do the service of the LORD.
04 8:12 The Levites shall lay their hands on the heads of the bulls, and he shall offer the one for a sin offering and the other for a burnt offering to the LORD, to make atonement for the Levites.
04 8:13 Then you shall have the Levites stand before Aaron and his sons, and you shall present them as an elevation offering to the LORD.
04 8:14 Thus you shall separate the Levites from among the other Israelites, and the Levites shall be mine.
04 8:15 Thereafter the Levites may go in to do service at the tent of meeting, once you have cleansed them and presented them as an elevation offering.
04 8:16 For they are unreservedly given to me from among the Israelites; I have taken them for myself, in place of all that open the womb, the firstborn of all the Israelites.
04 8:17 For all the firstborn among the Israelites are mine, both human and animal. On the day that I struck down all the firstborn in the land of Egypt I consecrated them for myself,
04 8:18 but I have taken the Levites in place of all the firstborn among the Israelites.
04 8:19 Moreover, I have given the Levites as a gift to Aaron and his sons from among the Israelites, to do the service for the Israelites at the tent of meeting, and to make atonement for the Israelites, in order that there may be no plague among the Israelites for coming too close to the sanctuary.
04 8:20 Moses and Aaron and the whole congregation of the Israelites did with the Levites accordingly; the Israelites did with the Levites just as the LORD had commanded Moses concerning them.
04 8:21 The Levites purified themselves from sin and washed their clothes; then Aaron presented them as an elevation offering before the LORD, and Aaron made atonement for them to cleanse them.
04 8:22 Thereafter the Levites went in to do their service in the tent of meeting in attendance on Aaron and his sons. As the LORD had commanded Moses concerning the Levites, so they did with them.
04 8:23 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 8:24 This applies to the Levites: from twenty-five years old and upward they shall begin to do duty in the service of the tent of meeting;
04 8:25 and from the age of fifty years they shall retire from the duty of the service and serve no more.
04 8:26 They may assist their brothers in the tent of meeting in carrying out their duties, but they shall perform no service. Thus you shall do with the Levites in assigning their duties.
04 9:1 The LORD spoke to Moses in the wilderness of Sinai, in the first month of the second year after they had come out of the land of Egypt, saying:
04 9:2 Let the Israelites keep the passover at its appointed time.
04 9:3 On the fourteenth day of this month, at twilight, you shall keep it at its appointed time; according to all its statutes and all its regulations you shall keep it.
04 9:4 So Moses told the Israelites that they should keep the passover.
04 9:5 They kept the passover in the first month, on the fourteenth day of the month, at twilight, in the wilderness of Sinai. Just as the LORD had commanded Moses, so the Israelites did.
04 9:6 Now there were certain people who were unclean through touching a corpse, so that they could not keep the passover on that day. They came before Moses and Aaron on that day,
04 9:7 and said to him, "Although we are unclean through touching a corpse, why must we be kept from presenting the LORD's offering at its appointed time among the Israelites?"
04 9:8 Moses spoke to them, "Wait, so that I may hear what the LORD will command concerning you."
04 9:9 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 9:10 Speak to the Israelites, saying: Anyone of you or your descendants who is unclean through touching a corpse, or is away on a journey, shall still keep the passover to the LORD.
04 9:11 In the second month on the fourteenth day, at twilight, they shall keep it; they shall eat it with unleavened bread and bitter herbs.
04 9:12 They shall leave none of it until morning, nor break a bone of it; according to all the statute for the passover they shall keep it.
04 9:13 But anyone who is clean and is not on a journey, and yet refrains from keeping the passover, shall be cut off from the people for not presenting the LORD's offering at its appointed time; such a one shall bear the consequences for the sin.
04 9:14 Any alien residing among you who wishes to keep the passover to the LORD shall do so according to the statute of the passover and according to its regulation; you shall have one statute for both the resident alien and the native.
04 9:15 On the day the tabernacle was set up, the cloud covered the tabernacle, the tent of the covenant; and from evening until morning it was over the tabernacle, having the appearance of fire.
04 9:16 It was always so: the cloud covered it by day and the appearance of fire by night.
04 9:17 Whenever the cloud lifted from over the tent, then the Israelites would set out; and in the place where the cloud settled down, there the Israelites would camp.
04 9:18 At the command of the LORD the Israelites would set out, and at the command of the LORD they would camp. As long as the cloud rested over the tabernacle, they would remain in camp.
04 9:19 Even when the cloud continued over the tabernacle many days, the Israelites would keep the charge of the LORD, and would not set out.
04 9:20 Sometimes the cloud would remain a few days over the tabernacle, and according to the command of the LORD they would remain in camp; then according to the command of the LORD they would set out.
04 9:21 Sometimes the cloud would remain from evening until morning; and when the cloud lifted in the morning, they would set out, or if it continued for a day and a night, when the cloud lifted they would set out.
04 9:22 Whether it was two days, or a month, or a longer time, that the cloud continued over the tabernacle, resting upon it, the Israelites would remain in camp and would not set out; but when it lifted they would set out.
04 9:23 At the command of the LORD they would camp, and at the command of the LORD they would set out. They kept the charge of the LORD, at the command of the LORD by Moses.
04 10:1 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 10:2 Make two silver trumpets; you shall make them of hammered work; and you shall use them for summoning the congregation, and for breaking camp.
04 10:3 When both are blown, the whole congregation shall assemble before you at the entrance of the tent of meeting.
04 10:4 But if only one is blown, then the leaders, the heads of the tribes of Israel, shall assemble before you.
04 10:5 When you blow an alarm, the camps on the east side shall set out;
04 10:6 when you blow a second alarm, the camps on the south side shall set out. An alarm is to be blown whenever they are to set out.
04 10:7 But when the assembly is to be gathered, you shall blow, but you shall not sound an alarm.
04 10:8 The sons of Aaron, the priests, shall blow the trumpets; this shall be a perpetual institution for you throughout your generations.
04 10:9 When you go to war in your land against the adversary who oppresses you, you shall sound an alarm with the trumpets, so that you may be remembered before the LORD your God and be saved from your enemies.
04 10:10 Also on your days of rejoicing, at your appointed festivals, and at the beginnings of your months, you shall blow the trumpets over your burnt offerings and over your sacrifices of well-being; they shall serve as a reminder on your behalf before the LORD your God: I am the LORD your God.
04 10:11 In the second year, in the second month, on the twentieth day of the month, the cloud lifted from over the tabernacle of the covenant.
04 10:12 Then the Israelites set out by stages from the wilderness of Sinai, and the cloud settled down in the wilderness of Paran.
04 10:13 They set out for the first time at the command of the LORD by Moses.
04 10:14 The standard of the camp of Judah set out first, company by company, and over the whole company was Nahshon son of Amminadab.
04 10:15 Over the company of the tribe of Issachar was Nethanel son of Zuar;
04 10:16 and over the company of the tribe of Zebulun was Eliab son of Helon.
04 10:17 Then the tabernacle was taken down, and the Gershonites and the Merarites, who carried the tabernacle, set out.
04 10:18 Next the standard of the camp of Reuben set out, company by company; and over the whole company was Elizur son of Shedeur.
04 10:19 Over the company of the tribe of Simeon was Shelumiel son of Zurishaddai,
04 10:20 and over the company of the tribe of Gad was Eliasaph son of Deuel.
04 10:21 Then the Kohathites, who carried the holy things, set out; and the tabernacle was set up before their arrival.
04 10:22 Next the standard of the Ephraimite camp set out, company by company, and over the whole company was Elishama son of Ammihud.
04 10:23 Over the company of the tribe of Manasseh was Gamaliel son of Pedahzur,
04 10:24 and over the company of the tribe of Benjamin was Abidan son of Gideoni.
04 10:25 Then the standard of the camp of Dan, acting as the rear guard of all the camps, set out, company by company, and over the whole company was Ahiezer son of Ammishaddai.
04 10:26 Over the company of the tribe of Asher was Pagiel son of Ochran,
04 10:27 and over the company of the tribe of Naphtali was Ahira son of Enan.
04 10:28 This was the order of march of the Israelites, company by company, when they set out.
04 10:29 Moses said to Hobab son of Reuel the Midianite, Moses' father-in-law, "We are setting out for the place of which the LORD said, 'I will give it to you'; come with us, and we will treat you well; for the LORD has promised good to Israel."
04 10:30 But he said to him, "I will not go, but I will go back to my own land and to my kindred."
04 10:31 He said, "Do not leave us, for you know where we should camp in the wilderness, and you will serve as eyes for us.
04 10:32 Moreover, if you go with us, whatever good the LORD does for us, the same we will do for you."
04 10:33 So they set out from the mount of the LORD three days' journey with the ark of the covenant of the LORD going before them three days' journey, to seek out a resting place for them,
04 10:34 the cloud of the LORD being over them by day when they set out from the camp.
04 10:35 Whenever the ark set out, Moses would say, "Arise, O LORD, let your enemies be scattered, and your foes flee before you."
04 10:36 And whenever it came to rest, he would say, "Return, O LORD of the ten thousand thousands of Israel."
04 11:1 Now when the people complained in the hearing of the LORD about their misfortunes, the LORD heard it and his anger was kindled. Then the fire of the LORD burned against them, and consumed some outlying parts of the camp.
04 11:2 But the people cried out to Moses; and Moses prayed to the LORD, and the fire abated.
04 11:3 So that place was called Taberah, because the fire of the LORD burned against them.
04 11:4 The rabble among them had a strong craving; and the Israelites also wept again, and said, "If only we had meat to eat!
04 11:5 We remember the fish we used to eat in Egypt for nothing, the cucumbers, the melons, the leeks, the onions, and the garlic;
04 11:6 but now our strength is dried up, and there is nothing at all but this manna to look at."
04 11:7 Now the manna was like coriander seed, and its color was like the color of gum resin.
04 11:8 The people went around and gathered it, ground it in mills or beat it in mortars, then boiled it in pots and made cakes of it; and the taste of it was like the taste of cakes baked with oil.
04 11:9 When the dew fell on the camp in the night, the manna would fall with it.
04 11:10 Moses heard the people weeping throughout their families, all at the entrances of their tents. Then the LORD became very angry, and Moses was displeased.
04 11:11 So Moses said to the LORD, "Why have you treated your servant so badly? Why have I not found favor in your sight, that you lay the burden of all this people on me?
04 11:12 Did I conceive all this people? Did I give birth to them, that you should say to me, 'Carry them in your bosom, as a nurse carries a sucking child,' to the land that you promised on oath to their ancestors?
04 11:13 Where am I to get meat to give to all this people? For they come weeping to me and say, 'Give us meat to eat!'
04 11:14 I am not able to carry all this people alone, for they are too heavy for me.
04 11:15 If this is the way you are going to treat me, put me to death at once--if I have found favor in your sight--and do not let me see my misery."
04 11:16 So the LORD said to Moses, "Gather for me seventy of the elders of Israel, whom you know to be the elders of the people and officers over them; bring them to the tent of meeting, and have them take their place there with you.
04 11:17 I will come down and talk with you there; and I will take some of the spirit that is on you and put it on them; and they shall bear the burden of the people along with you so that you will not bear it all by yourself.
04 11:18 And say to the people: Consecrate yourselves for tomorrow, and you shall eat meat; for you have wailed in the hearing of the LORD, saying, 'If only we had meat to eat! Surely it was better for us in Egypt.' Therefore the LORD will give you meat, and you shall eat.
04 11:19 You shall eat not only one day, or two days, or five days, or ten days, or twenty days,
04 11:20 but for a whole month--until it comes out of your nostrils and becomes loathsome to you--because you have rejected the LORD who is among you, and have wailed before him, saying, 'Why did we ever leave Egypt?'"
04 11:21 But Moses said, "The people I am with number six hundred thousand on foot; and you say, 'I will give them meat, that they may eat for a whole month'!
04 11:22 Are there enough flocks and herds to slaughter for them? Are there enough fish in the sea to catch for them?"
04 11:23 The LORD said to Moses, "Is the LORD's power limited? Now you shall see whether my word will come true for you or not."
04 11:24 So Moses went out and told the people the words of the LORD; and he gathered seventy elders of the people, and placed them all around the tent.
04 11:25 Then the LORD came down in the cloud and spoke to him, and took some of the spirit that was on him and put it on the seventy elders; and when the spirit rested upon them, they prophesied. But they did not do so again.
04 11:26 Two men remained in the camp, one named Eldad, and the other named Medad, and the spirit rested on them; they were among those registered, but they had not gone out to the tent, and so they prophesied in the camp.
04 11:27 And a young man ran and told Moses, "Eldad and Medad are prophesying in the camp."
04 11:28 And Joshua son of Nun, the assistant of Moses, one of his chosen men, said, "My lord Moses, stop them!"
04 11:29 But Moses said to him, "Are you jealous for my sake? Would that all the LORD's people were prophets, and that the LORD would put his spirit on them!"
04 11:30 And Moses and the elders of Israel returned to the camp.
04 11:31 Then a wind went out from the LORD, and it brought quails from the sea and let them fall beside the camp, about a day's journey on this side and a day's journey on the other side, all around the camp, about two cubits deep on the ground.
04 11:32 So the people worked all that day and night and all the next day, gathering the quails; the least anyone gathered was ten homers; and they spread them out for themselves all around the camp.
04 11:33 But while the meat was still between their teeth, before it was consumed, the anger of the LORD was kindled against the people, and the LORD struck the people with a very great plague.
04 11:34 So that place was called Kibroth-hattaavah, because there they buried the people who had the craving.
04 11:35 From Kibroth-hattaavah the people journeyed to Hazeroth.
04 12:1 While they were at Hazeroth, Miriam and Aaron spoke against Moses because of the Cushite woman whom he had married (for he had indeed married a Cushite woman);
04 12:2 and they said, "Has the LORD spoken only through Moses? Has he not spoken through us also?" And the LORD heard it.
04 12:3 Now the man Moses was very humble, more so than anyone else on the face of the earth.
04 12:4 Suddenly the LORD said to Moses, Aaron, and Miriam, "Come out, you three, to the tent of meeting." So the three of them came out.
04 12:5 Then the LORD came down in a pillar of cloud, and stood at the entrance of the tent, and called Aaron and Miriam; and they both came forward.
04 12:6 And he said, "Hear my words: When there are prophets among you, I the LORD make myself known to them in visions; I speak to them in dreams.
04 12:7 Not so with my servant Moses; he is entrusted with all my house.
04 12:8 With him I speak face to face--clearly, not in riddles; and he beholds the form of the LORD. Why then were you not afraid to speak against my servant Moses?"
04 12:9 And the anger of the LORD was kindled against them, and he departed.
04 12:10 When the cloud went away from over the tent, Miriam had become leprous, as white as snow. And Aaron turned towards Miriam and saw that she was leprous.
04 12:11 Then Aaron said to Moses, "Oh, my lord, do not punish us for a sin that we have so foolishly committed.
04 12:12 Do not let her be like one stillborn, whose flesh is half consumed when it comes out of its mother's womb."
04 12:13 And Moses cried to the LORD, "O God, please heal her."
04 12:14 But the LORD said to Moses, "If her father had but spit in her face, would she not bear her shame for seven days? Let her be shut out of the camp for seven days, and after that she may be brought in again."
04 12:15 So Miriam was shut out of the camp for seven days; and the people did not set out on the march until Miriam had been brought in again.
04 12:16 After that the people set out from Hazeroth, and camped in the wilderness of Paran.
04 13:1 The LORD said to Moses,
04 13:2 "Send men to spy out the land of Canaan, which I am giving to the Israelites; from each of their ancestral tribes you shall send a man, every one a leader among them."
04 13:3 So Moses sent them from the wilderness of Paran, according to the command of the LORD, all of them leading men among the Israelites.
04 13:4 These were their names: From the tribe of Reuben, Shammua son of Zaccur;
04 13:5 from the tribe of Simeon, Shaphat son of Hori;
04 13:6 from the tribe of Judah, Caleb son of Jephunneh;
04 13:7 from the tribe of Issachar, Igal son of Joseph;
04 13:8 from the tribe of Ephraim, Hoshea son of Nun;
04 13:9 from the tribe of Benjamin, Palti son of Raphu;
04 13:10 from the tribe of Zebulun, Gaddiel son of Sodi;
04 13:11 from the tribe of Joseph (that is, from the tribe of Manasseh), Gaddi son of Susi;
04 13:12 from the tribe of Dan, Ammiel son of Gemalli;
04 13:13 from the tribe of Asher, Sethur son of Michael;
04 13:14 from the tribe of Naphtali, Nahbi son of Vophsi;
04 13:15 from the tribe of Gad, Geuel son of Machi.
04 13:16 These were the names of the men whom Moses sent to spy out the land. And Moses changed the name of Hoshea son of Nun to Joshua.
04 13:17 Moses sent them to spy out the land of Canaan, and said to them, "Go up there into the Negeb, and go up into the hill country,
04 13:18 and see what the land is like, and whether the people who live in it are strong or weak, whether they are few or many,
04 13:19 and whether the land they live in is good or bad, and whether the towns that they live in are unwalled or fortified,
04 13:20 and whether the land is rich or poor, and whether there are trees in it or not. Be bold, and bring some of the fruit of the land." Now it was the season of the first ripe grapes.
04 13:21 So they went up and spied out the land from the wilderness of Zin to Rehob, near Lebo-hamath.
04 13:22 They went up into the Negeb, and came to Hebron; and Ahiman, Sheshai, and Talmai, the Anakites, were there. (Hebron was built seven years before Zoan in Egypt.)
04 13:23 And they came to the Wadi Eshcol, and cut down from there a branch with a single cluster of grapes, and they carried it on a pole between two of them. They also brought some pomegranates and figs.
04 13:24 That place was called the Wadi Eshcol, because of the cluster that the Israelites cut down from there.
04 13:25 At the end of forty days they returned from spying out the land.
04 13:26 And they came to Moses and Aaron and to all the congregation of the Israelites in the wilderness of Paran, at Kadesh; they brought back word to them and to all the congregation, and showed them the fruit of the land.
04 13:27 And they told him, "We came to the land to which you sent us; it flows with milk and honey, and this is its fruit.
04 13:28 Yet the people who live in the land are strong, and the towns are fortified and very large; and besides, we saw the descendants of Anak there.
04 13:29 The Amalekites live in the land of the Negeb; the Hittites, the Jebusites, and the Amorites live in the hill country; and the Canaanites live by the sea, and along the Jordan."
04 13:30 But Caleb quieted the people before Moses, and said, "Let us go up at once and occupy it, for we are well able to overcome it."
04 13:31 Then the men who had gone up with him said, "We are not able to go up against this people, for they are stronger than we."
04 13:32 So they brought to the Israelites an unfavorable report of the land that they had spied out, saying, "The land that we have gone through as spies is a land that devours its inhabitants; and all the people that we saw in it are of great size.
04 13:33 There we saw the Nephilim (the Anakites come from the Nephilim); and to ourselves we seemed like grasshoppers, and so we seemed to them."
04 14:1 Then all the congregation raised a loud cry, and the people wept that night.
04 14:2 And all the Israelites complained against Moses and Aaron; the whole congregation said to them, "Would that we had died in the land of Egypt! Or would that we had died in this wilderness!
04 14:3 Why is the LORD bringing us into this land to fall by the sword? Our wives and our little ones will become booty; would it not be better for us to go back to Egypt?"
04 14:4 So they said to one another, "Let us choose a captain, and go back to Egypt."
04 14:5 Then Moses and Aaron fell on their faces before all the assembly of the congregation of the Israelites.
04 14:6 And Joshua son of Nun and Caleb son of Jephunneh, who were among those who had spied out the land, tore their clothes
04 14:7 and said to all the congregation of the Israelites, "The land that we went through as spies is an exceedingly good land.
04 14:8 If the LORD is pleased with us, he will bring us into this land and give it to us, a land that flows with milk and honey.
04 14:9 Only, do not rebel against the LORD; and do not fear the people of the land, for they are no more than bread for us; their protection is removed from them, and the LORD is with us; do not fear them."
04 14:10 But the whole congregation threatened to stone them. Then the glory of the LORD appeared at the tent of meeting to all the Israelites.
04 14:11 And the LORD said to Moses, "How long will this people despise me? And how long will they refuse to believe in me, in spite of all the signs that I have done among them?
04 14:12 I will strike them with pestilence and disinherit them, and I will make of you a nation greater and mightier than they."
04 14:13 But Moses said to the LORD, "Then the Egyptians will hear of it, for in your might you brought up this people from among them,
04 14:14 and they will tell the inhabitants of this land. They have heard that you, O LORD, are in the midst of this people; for you, O LORD, are seen face to face, and your cloud stands over them and you go in front of them, in a pillar of cloud by day and in a pillar of fire by night.
04 14:15 Now if you kill this people all at one time, then the nations who have heard about you will say,
04 14:16 'It is because the LORD was not able to bring this people into the land he swore to give them that he has slaughtered them in the wilderness.'
04 14:17 And now, therefore, let the power of the LORD be great in the way that you promised when you spoke, saying,
04 14:18 'The LORD is slow to anger, and abounding in steadfast love, forgiving iniquity and transgression, but by no means clearing the guilty, visiting the iniquity of the parents upon the children to the third and the fourth generation.'
04 14:19 Forgive the iniquity of this people according to the greatness of your steadfast love, just as you have pardoned this people, from Egypt even until now."
04 14:20 Then the LORD said, "I do forgive, just as you have asked;
04 14:21 nevertheless--as I live, and as all the earth shall be filled with the glory of the LORD--
04 14:22 none of the people who have seen my glory and the signs that I did in Egypt and in the wilderness, and yet have tested me these ten times and have not obeyed my voice,
04 14:23 shall see the land that I swore to give to their ancestors; none of those who despised me shall see it.
04 14:24 But my servant Caleb, because he has a different spirit and has followed me wholeheartedly, I will bring into the land into which he went, and his descendants shall possess it.
04 14:25 Now, since the Amalekites and the Canaanites live in the valleys, turn tomorrow and set out for the wilderness by the way to the Red Sea."
04 14:26 And the LORD spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying:
04 14:27 How long shall this wicked congregation complain against me? I have heard the complaints of the Israelites, which they complain against me.
04 14:28 Say to them, "As I live," says the LORD, "I will do to you the very things I heard you say:
04 14:29 your dead bodies shall fall in this very wilderness; and of all your number, included in the census, from twenty years old and upward, who have complained against me,
04 14:30 not one of you shall come into the land in which I swore to settle you, except Caleb son of Jephunneh and Joshua son of Nun.
04 14:31 But your little ones, who you said would become booty, I will bring in, and they shall know the land that you have despised.
04 14:32 But as for you, your dead bodies shall fall in this wilderness.
04 14:33 And your children shall be shepherds in the wilderness for forty years, and shall suffer for your faithlessness, until the last of your dead bodies lies in the wilderness.
04 14:34 According to the number of the days in which you spied out the land, forty days, for every day a year, you shall bear your iniquity, forty years, and you shall know my displeasure."
04 14:35 I the LORD have spoken; surely I will do thus to all this wicked congregation gathered together against me: in this wilderness they shall come to a full end, and there they shall die.
04 14:36 And the men whom Moses sent to spy out the land, who returned and made all the congregation complain against him by bringing a bad report about the land--
04 14:37 the men who brought an unfavorable report about the land died by a plague before the LORD.
04 14:38 But Joshua son of Nun and Caleb son of Jephunneh alone remained alive, of those men who went to spy out the land.
04 14:39 When Moses told these words to all the Israelites, the people mourned greatly.
04 14:40 They rose early in the morning and went up to the heights of the hill country, saying, "Here we are. We will go up to the place that the LORD has promised, for we have sinned."
04 14:41 But Moses said, "Why do you continue to transgress the command of the LORD? That will not succeed.
04 14:42 Do not go up, for the LORD is not with you; do not let yourselves be struck down before your enemies.
04 14:43 For the Amalekites and the Canaanites will confront you there, and you shall fall by the sword; because you have turned back from following the LORD, the LORD will not be with you."
04 14:44 But they presumed to go up to the heights of the hill country, even though the ark of the covenant of the LORD, and Moses, had not left the camp.
04 14:45 Then the Amalekites and the Canaanites who lived in that hill country came down and defeated them, pursuing them as far as Hormah.
04 15:1 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 15:2 Speak to the Israelites and say to them: When you come into the land you are to inhabit, which I am giving you,
04 15:3 and you make an offering by fire to the LORD from the herd or from the flock--whether a burnt offering or a sacrifice, to fulfill a vow or as a freewill offering or at your appointed festivals--to make a pleasing odor for the LORD,
04 15:4 then whoever presents such an offering to the LORD shall present also a grain offering, one-tenth of an ephah of choice flour, mixed with one-fourth of a hin of oil.
04 15:5 Moreover, you shall offer one-fourth of a hin of wine as a drink offering with the burnt offering or the sacrifice, for each lamb.
04 15:6 For a ram, you shall offer a grain offering, two-tenths of an ephah of choice flour mixed with one-third of a hin of oil;
04 15:7 and as a drink offering you shall offer one-third of a hin of wine, a pleasing odor to the LORD.
04 15:8 When you offer a bull as a burnt offering or a sacrifice, to fulfill a vow or as an offering of well-being to the LORD,
04 15:9 then you shall present with the bull a grain offering, three-tenths of an ephah of choice flour, mixed with half a hin of oil,
04 15:10 and you shall present as a drink offering half a hin of wine, as an offering by fire, a pleasing odor to the LORD.
04 15:11 Thus it shall be done for each ox or ram, or for each of the male lambs or the kids.
04 15:12 According to the number that you offer, so you shall do with each and every one.
04 15:13 Every native Israelite shall do these things in this way, in presenting an offering by fire, a pleasing odor to the LORD.
04 15:14 An alien who lives with you, or who takes up permanent residence among you, and wishes to offer an offering by fire, a pleasing odor to the LORD, shall do as you do.
04 15:15 As for the assembly, there shall be for both you and the resident alien a single statute, a perpetual statute throughout your generations; you and the alien shall be alike before the LORD.
04 15:16 You and the alien who resides with you shall have the same law and the same ordinance.
04 15:17 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 15:18 Speak to the Israelites and say to them: After you come into the land to which I am bringing you,
04 15:19 whenever you eat of the bread of the land, you shall present a donation to the LORD.
04 15:20 From your first batch of dough you shall present a loaf as a donation; you shall present it just as you present a donation from the threshing floor.
04 15:21 Throughout your generations you shall give to the LORD a donation from the first of your batch of dough.
04 15:22 But if you unintentionally fail to observe all these commandments that the LORD has spoken to Moses--
04 15:23 everything that the LORD has commanded you by Moses, from the day the LORD gave commandment and thereafter, throughout your generations--
04 15:24 then if it was done unintentionally without the knowledge of the congregation, the whole congregation shall offer one young bull for a burnt offering, a pleasing odor to the LORD, together with its grain offering and its drink offering, according to the ordinance, and one male goat for a sin offering.
04 15:25 The priest shall make atonement for all the congregation of the Israelites, and they shall be forgiven; it was unintentional, and they have brought their offering, an offering by fire to the LORD, and their sin offering before the LORD, for their error.
04 15:26 All the congregation of the Israelites shall be forgiven, as well as the aliens residing among them, because the whole people was involved in the error.
04 15:27 An individual who sins unintentionally shall present a female goat a year old for a sin offering.
04 15:28 And the priest shall make atonement before the LORD for the one who commits an error, when it is unintentional, to make atonement for the person, who then shall be forgiven.
04 15:29 For both the native among the Israelites and the alien residing among them--you shall have the same law for anyone who acts in error.
04 15:30 But whoever acts high-handedly, whether a native or an alien, affronts the LORD, and shall be cut off from among the people.
04 15:31 Because of having despised the word of the LORD and broken his commandment, such a person shall be utterly cut off and bear the guilt.
04 15:32 When the Israelites were in the wilderness, they found a man gathering sticks on the sabbath day.
04 15:33 Those who found him gathering sticks brought him to Moses, Aaron, and to the whole congregation.
04 15:34 They put him in custody, because it was not clear what should be done to him.
04 15:35 Then the LORD said to Moses, "The man shall be put to death; all the congregation shall stone him outside the camp."
04 15:36 The whole congregation brought him outside the camp and stoned him to death, just as the LORD had commanded Moses.
04 15:37 The LORD said to Moses:
04 15:38 Speak to the Israelites, and tell them to make fringes on the corners of their garments throughout their generations and to put a blue cord on the fringe at each corner.
04 15:39 You have the fringe so that, when you see it, you will remember all the commandments of the LORD and do them, and not follow the lust of your own heart and your own eyes.
04 15:40 So you shall remember and do all my commandments, and you shall be holy to your God.
04 15:41 I am the LORD your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, to be your God: I am the LORD your God.
04 16:1 Now Korah son of Izhar son of Kohath son of Levi, along with Dathan and Abiram sons of Eliab, and On son of Peleth--descendants of Reuben--took
04 16:2 two hundred fifty Israelite men, leaders of the congregation, chosen from the assembly, well-known men, and they confronted Moses.
04 16:3 They assembled against Moses and against Aaron, and said to them, "You have gone too far! All the congregation are holy, everyone of them, and the LORD is among them. So why then do you exalt yourselves above the assembly of the LORD?"
04 16:4 When Moses heard it, he fell on his face.
04 16:5 Then he said to Korah and all his company, "In the morning the LORD will make known who is his, and who is holy, and who will be allowed to approach him; the one whom he will choose he will allow to approach him.
04 16:6 Do this: take censers, Korah and all your company,
04 16:7 and tomorrow put fire in them, and lay incense on them before the LORD; and the man whom the LORD chooses shall be the holy one. You Levites have gone too far!"
04 16:8 Then Moses said to Korah, "Hear now, you Levites!
04 16:9 Is it too little for you that the God of Israel has separated you from the congregation of Israel, to allow you to approach him in order to perform the duties of the LORD's tabernacle, and to stand before the congregation and serve them?
04 16:10 He has allowed you to approach him, and all your brother Levites with you; yet you seek the priesthood as well!
04 16:11 Therefore you and all your company have gathered together against the LORD. What is Aaron that you rail against him?"
04 16:12 Moses sent for Dathan and Abiram sons of Eliab; but they said, "We will not come!
04 16:13 Is it too little that you have brought us up out of a land flowing with milk and honey to kill us in the wilderness, that you must also lord it over us?
04 16:14 It is clear you have not brought us into a land flowing with milk and honey, or given us an inheritance of fields and vineyards. Would you put out the eyes of these men? We will not come!"
04 16:15 Moses was very angry and said to the LORD, "Pay no attention to their offering. I have not taken one donkey from them, and I have not harmed any one of them."
04 16:16 And Moses said to Korah, "As for you and all your company, be present tomorrow before the LORD, you and they and Aaron;
04 16:17 and let each one of you take his censer, and put incense on it, and each one of you present his censer before the LORD, two hundred fifty censers; you also, and Aaron, each his censer."
04 16:18 So each man took his censer, and they put fire in the censers and laid incense on them, and they stood at the entrance of the tent of meeting with Moses and Aaron.
04 16:19 Then Korah assembled the whole congregation against them at the entrance of the tent of meeting. And the glory of the LORD appeared to the whole congregation.
04 16:20 Then the LORD spoke to Moses and to Aaron, saying:
04 16:21 Separate yourselves from this congregation, so that I may consume them in a moment.
04 16:22 They fell on their faces, and said, "O God, the God of the spirits of all flesh, shall one person sin and you become angry with the whole congregation?"
04 16:23 And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 16:24 Say to the congregation: Get away from the dwellings of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram.
04 16:25 So Moses got up and went to Dathan and Abiram; the elders of Israel followed him.
04 16:26 He said to the congregation, "Turn away from the tents of these wicked men, and touch nothing of theirs, or you will be swept away for all their sins."
04 16:27 So they got away from the dwellings of Korah, Dathan, and Abiram; and Dathan and Abiram came out and stood at the entrance of their tents, together with their wives, their children, and their little ones.
04 16:28 And Moses said, "This is how you shall know that the LORD has sent me to do all these works; it has not been of my own accord:
04 16:29 If these people die a natural death, or if a natural fate comes on them, then the LORD has not sent me.
04 16:30 But if the LORD creates something new, and the ground opens its mouth and swallows them up, with all that belongs to them, and they go down alive into Sheol, then you shall know that these men have despised the LORD."
04 16:31 As soon as he finished speaking all these words, the ground under them was split apart.
04 16:32 The earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up, along with their households--everyone who belonged to Korah and all their goods.
04 16:33 So they with all that belonged to them went down alive into Sheol; the earth closed over them, and they perished from the midst of the assembly.
04 16:34 All Israel around them fled at their outcry, for they said, "The earth will swallow us too!"
04 16:35 And fire came out from the LORD and consumed the two hundred fifty men offering the incense.
04 16:36 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 16:37 Tell Eleazar son of Aaron the priest to take the censers out of the blaze; then scatter the fire far and wide.
04 16:38 For the censers of these sinners have become holy at the cost of their lives. Make them into hammered plates as a covering for the altar, for they presented them before the LORD and they became holy. Thus they shall be a sign to the Israelites.
04 16:39 So Eleazar the priest took the bronze censers that had been presented by those who were burned; and they were hammered out as a covering for the altar--
04 16:40 a reminder to the Israelites that no outsider, who is not of the descendants of Aaron, shall approach to offer incense before the LORD, so as not to become like Korah and his company--just as the LORD had said to him through Moses.
04 16:41 On the next day, however, the whole congregation of the Israelites rebelled against Moses and against Aaron, saying, "You have killed the people of the LORD."
04 16:42 And when the congregation had assembled against them, Moses and Aaron turned toward the tent of meeting; the cloud had covered it and the glory of the LORD appeared.
04 16:43 Then Moses and Aaron came to the front of the tent of meeting,
04 16:44 and the LORD spoke to Moses, saying,
04 16:45 "Get away from this congregation, so that I may consume them in a moment." And they fell on their faces.
04 16:46 Moses said to Aaron, "Take your censer, put fire on it from the altar and lay incense on it, and carry it quickly to the congregation and make atonement for them. For wrath has gone out from the LORD; the plague has begun."
04 16:47 So Aaron took it as Moses had ordered, and ran into the middle of the assembly, where the plague had already begun among the people. He put on the incense, and made atonement for the people.
04 16:48 He stood between the dead and the living; and the plague was stopped.
04 16:49 Those who died by the plague were fourteen thousand seven hundred, besides those who died in the affair of Korah.
04 16:50 When the plague was stopped, Aaron returned to Moses at the entrance of the tent of meeting.
04 17:1 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 17:2 Speak to the Israelites, and get twelve staffs from them, one for each ancestral house, from all the leaders of their ancestral houses. Write each man's name on his staff,
04 17:3 and write Aaron's name on the staff of Levi. For there shall be one staff for the head of each ancestral house.
04 17:4 Place them in the tent of meeting before the covenant, where I meet with you.
04 17:5 And the staff of the man whom I choose shall sprout; thus I will put a stop to the complaints of the Israelites that they continually make against you.
04 17:6 Moses spoke to the Israelites; and all their leaders gave him staffs, one for each leader, according to their ancestral houses, twelve staffs; and the staff of Aaron was among theirs.
04 17:7 So Moses placed the staffs before the LORD in the tent of the covenant.
04 17:8 When Moses went into the tent of the covenant on the next day, the staff of Aaron for the house of Levi had sprouted. It put forth buds, produced blossoms, and bore ripe almonds.
04 17:9 Then Moses brought out all the staffs from before the LORD to all the Israelites; and they looked, and each man took his staff.
04 17:10 And the LORD said to Moses, "Put back the staff of Aaron before the covenant, to be kept as a warning to rebels, so that you may make an end of their complaints against me, or else they will die."
04 17:11 Moses did so; just as the LORD commanded him, so he did.
04 17:12 The Israelites said to Moses, "We are perishing; we are lost, all of us are lost!
04 17:13 Everyone who approaches the tabernacle of the LORD will die. Are we all to perish?"
04 18:1 The LORD said to Aaron: You and your sons and your ancestral house with you shall bear responsibility for offenses connected with the sanctuary, while you and your sons alone shall bear responsibility for offenses connected with the priesthood.
04 18:2 So bring with you also your brothers of the tribe of Levi, your ancestral tribe, in order that they may be joined to you, and serve you while you and your sons with you are in front of the tent of the covenant.
04 18:3 They shall perform duties for you and for the whole tent. But they must not approach either the utensils of the sanctuary or the altar, otherwise both they and you will die.
04 18:4 They are attached to you in order to perform the duties of the tent of meeting, for all the service of the tent; no outsider shall approach you.
04 18:5 You yourselves shall perform the duties of the sanctuary and the duties of the altar, so that wrath may never again come upon the Israelites.
04 18:6 It is I who now take your brother Levites from among the Israelites; they are now yours as a gift, dedicated to the LORD, to perform the service of the tent of meeting.
04 18:7 But you and your sons with you shall diligently perform your priestly duties in all that concerns the altar and the area behind the curtain. I give your priesthood as a gift; any outsider who approaches shall be put to death.
04 18:8 The LORD spoke to Aaron: I have given you charge of the offerings made to me, all the holy gifts of the Israelites; I have given them to you and your sons as a priestly portion due you in perpetuity.
04 18:9 This shall be yours from the most holy things, reserved from the fire: every offering of theirs that they render to me as a most holy thing, whether grain offering, sin offering, or guilt offering, shall belong to you and your sons.
04 18:10 As a most holy thing you shall eat it; every male may eat it; it shall be holy to you.
04 18:11 This also is yours: I have given to you, together with your sons and daughters, as a perpetual due, whatever is set aside from the gifts of all the elevation offerings of the Israelites; everyone who is clean in your house may eat them.
04 18:12 All the best of the oil and all the best of the wine and of the grain, the choice produce that they give to the LORD, I have given to you.
04 18:13 The first fruits of all that is in their land, which they bring to the LORD, shall be yours; everyone who is clean in your house may eat of it.
04 18:14 Every devoted thing in Israel shall be yours.
04 18:15 The first issue of the womb of all creatures, human and animal, which is offered to the LORD, shall be yours; but the firstborn of human beings you shall redeem, and the firstborn of unclean animals you shall redeem.
04 18:16 Their redemption price, reckoned from one month of age, you shall fix at five shekels of silver, according to the shekel of the sanctuary (that is, twenty gerahs).
04 18:17 But the firstborn of a cow, or the firstborn of a sheep, or the firstborn of a goat, you shall not redeem; they are holy. You shall dash their blood on the altar, and shall turn their fat into smoke as an offering by fire for a pleasing odor to the LORD;
04 18:18 but their flesh shall be yours, just as the breast that is elevated and as the right thigh are yours.
04 18:19 All the holy offerings that the Israelites present to the LORD I have given to you, together with your sons and daughters, as a perpetual due; it is a covenant of salt forever before the LORD for you and your descendants as well.
04 18:20 Then the LORD said to Aaron: You shall have no allotment in their land, nor shall you have any share among them; I am your share and your possession among the Israelites.
04 18:21 To the Levites I have given every tithe in Israel for a possession in return for the service that they perform, the service in the tent of meeting.
04 18:22 From now on the Israelites shall no longer approach the tent of meeting, or else they will incur guilt and die.
04 18:23 But the Levites shall perform the service of the tent of meeting, and they shall bear responsibility for their own offenses; it shall be a perpetual statute throughout your generations. But among the Israelites they shall have no allotment,
04 18:24 because I have given to the Levites as their portion the tithe of the Israelites, which they set apart as an offering to the LORD. Therefore I have said of them that they shall have no allotment among the Israelites.
04 18:25 Then the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 18:26 You shall speak to the Levites, saying: When you receive from the Israelites the tithe that I have given you from them for your portion, you shall set apart an offering from it to the LORD, a tithe of the tithe.
04 18:27 It shall be reckoned to you as your gift, the same as the grain of the threshing floor and the fullness of the wine press.
04 18:28 Thus you also shall set apart an offering to the LORD from all the tithes that you receive from the Israelites; and from them you shall give the LORD's offering to the priest Aaron.
04 18:29 Out of all the gifts to you, you shall set apart every offering due to the LORD; the best of all of them is the part to be consecrated.
04 18:30 Say also to them: When you have set apart the best of it, then the rest shall be reckoned to the Levites as produce of the threshing floor, and as produce of the wine press.
04 18:31 You may eat it in any place, you and your households; for it is your payment for your service in the tent of meeting.
04 18:32 You shall incur no guilt by reason of it, when you have offered the best of it. But you shall not profane the holy gifts of the Israelites, on pain of death.
04 19:1 The LORD spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying:
04 19:2 This is a statute of the law that the LORD has commanded: Tell the Israelites to bring you a red heifer without defect, in which there is no blemish and on which no yoke has been laid.
04 19:3 You shall give it to the priest Eleazar, and it shall be taken outside the camp and slaughtered in his presence.
04 19:4 The priest Eleazar shall take some of its blood with his finger and sprinkle it seven times towards the front of the tent of meeting.
04 19:5 Then the heifer shall be burned in his sight; its skin, its flesh, and its blood, with its dung, shall be burned.
04 19:6 The priest shall take cedarwood, hyssop, and crimson material, and throw them into the fire in which the heifer is burning.
04 19:7 Then the priest shall wash his clothes and bathe his body in water, and afterwards he may come into the camp; but the priest shall remain unclean until evening.
04 19:8 The one who burns the heifer shall wash his clothes in water and bathe his body in water; he shall remain unclean until evening.
04 19:9 Then someone who is clean shall gather up the ashes of the heifer, and deposit them outside the camp in a clean place; and they shall be kept for the congregation of the Israelites for the water for cleansing. It is a purification offering.
04 19:10 The one who gathers the ashes of the heifer shall wash his clothes and be unclean until evening. This shall be a perpetual statute for the Israelites and for the alien residing among them.
04 19:11 Those who touch the dead body of any human being shall be unclean seven days.
04 19:12 They shall purify themselves with the water on the third day and on the seventh day, and so be clean; but if they do not purify themselves on the third day and on the seventh day, they will not become clean.
04 19:13 All who touch a corpse, the body of a human being who has died, and do not purify themselves, defile the tabernacle of the LORD; such persons shall be cut off from Israel. Since water for cleansing was not dashed on them, they remain unclean; their uncleanness is still on them.
04 19:14 This is the law when someone dies in a tent: everyone who comes into the tent, and everyone who is in the tent, shall be unclean seven days.
04 19:15 And every open vessel with no cover fastened on it is unclean.
04 19:16 Whoever in the open field touches one who has been killed by a sword, or who has died naturally, or a human bone, or a grave, shall be unclean seven days.
04 19:17 For the unclean they shall take some ashes of the burnt purification offering, and running water shall be added in a vessel;
04 19:18 then a clean person shall take hyssop, dip it in the water, and sprinkle it on the tent, on all the furnishings, on the persons who were there, and on whoever touched the bone, the slain, the corpse, or the grave.
04 19:19 The clean person shall sprinkle the unclean ones on the third day and on the seventh day, thus purifying them on the seventh day. Then they shall wash their clothes and bathe themselves in water, and at evening they shall be clean.
04 19:20 Any who are unclean but do not purify themselves, those persons shall be cut off from the assembly, for they have defiled the sanctuary of the LORD. Since the water for cleansing has not been dashed on them, they are unclean.
04 19:21 It shall be a perpetual statute for them. The one who sprinkles the water for cleansing shall wash his clothes, and whoever touches the water for cleansing shall be unclean until evening.
04 19:22 Whatever the unclean person touches shall be unclean, and anyone who touches it shall be unclean until evening.
04 20:1 The Israelites, the whole congregation, came into the wilderness of Zin in the first month, and the people stayed in Kadesh. Miriam died there, and was buried there.
04 20:2 Now there was no water for the congregation; so they gathered together against Moses and against Aaron.
04 20:3 The people quarreled with Moses and said, "Would that we had died when our kindred died before the LORD!
04 20:4 Why have you brought the assembly of the LORD into this wilderness for us and our livestock to die here?
04 20:5 Why have you brought us up out of Egypt, to bring us to this wretched place? It is no place for grain, or figs, or vines, or pomegranates; and there is no water to drink."
04 20:6 Then Moses and Aaron went away from the assembly to the entrance of the tent of meeting; they fell on their faces, and the glory of the LORD appeared to them.
04 20:7 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 20:8 Take the staff, and assemble the congregation, you and your brother Aaron, and command the rock before their eyes to yield its water. Thus you shall bring water out of the rock for them; thus you shall provide drink for the congregation and their livestock.
04 20:9 So Moses took the staff from before the LORD, as he had commanded him.
04 20:10 Moses and Aaron gathered the assembly together before the rock, and he said to them, "Listen, you rebels, shall we bring water for you out of this rock?"
04 20:11 Then Moses lifted up his hand and struck the rock twice with his staff; water came out abundantly, and the congregation and their livestock drank.
04 20:12 But the LORD said to Moses and Aaron, "Because you did not trust in me, to show my holiness before the eyes of the Israelites, therefore you shall not bring this assembly into the land that I have given them."
04 20:13 These are the waters of Meribah, where the people of Israel quarreled with the LORD, and by which he showed his holiness.
04 20:14 Moses sent messengers from Kadesh to the king of Edom, "Thus says your brother Israel: You know all the adversity that has befallen us:
04 20:15 how our ancestors went down to Egypt, and we lived in Egypt a long time; and the Egyptians oppressed us and our ancestors;
04 20:16 and when we cried to the LORD, he heard our voice, and sent an angel and brought us out of Egypt; and here we are in Kadesh, a town on the edge of your territory.
04 20:17 Now let us pass through your land. We will not pass through field or vineyard, or drink water from any well; we will go along the King's Highway, not turning aside to the right hand or to the left until we have passed through your territory."
04 20:18 But Edom said to him, "You shall not pass through, or we will come out with the sword against you."
04 20:19 The Israelites said to him, "We will stay on the highway; and if we drink of your water, we and our livestock, then we will pay for it. It is only a small matter; just let us pass through on foot."
04 20:20 But he said, "You shall not pass through." And Edom came out against them with a large force, heavily armed.
04 20:21 Thus Edom refused to give Israel passage through their territory; so Israel turned away from them.
04 20:22 They set out from Kadesh, and the Israelites, the whole congregation, came to Mount Hor.
04 20:23 Then the LORD said to Moses and Aaron at Mount Hor, on the border of the land of Edom,
04 20:24 "Let Aaron be gathered to his people. For he shall not enter the land that I have given to the Israelites, because you rebelled against my command at the waters of Meribah.
04 20:25 Take Aaron and his son Eleazar, and bring them up Mount Hor;
04 20:26 strip Aaron of his vestments, and put them on his son Eleazar. But Aaron shall be gathered to his people, and shall die there."
04 20:27 Moses did as the LORD had commanded; they went up Mount Hor in the sight of the whole congregation.
04 20:28 Moses stripped Aaron of his vestments, and put them on his son Eleazar; and Aaron died there on the top of the mountain. Moses and Eleazar came down from the mountain.
04 20:29 When all the congregation saw that Aaron had died, all the house of Israel mourned for Aaron thirty days.
04 21:1 When the Canaanite, the king of Arad, who lived in the Negeb, heard that Israel was coming by the way of Atharim, he fought against Israel and took some of them captive.
04 21:2 Then Israel made a vow to the LORD and said, "If you will indeed give this people into our hands, then we will utterly destroy their towns."
04 21:3 The LORD listened to the voice of Israel, and handed over the Canaanites; and they utterly destroyed them and their towns; so the place was called Hormah.
04 21:4 From Mount Hor they set out by the way to the Red Sea, to go around the land of Edom; but the people became impatient on the way.
04 21:5 The people spoke against God and against Moses, "Why have you brought us up out of Egypt to die in the wilderness? For there is no food and no water, and we detest this miserable food."
04 21:6 Then the LORD sent poisonous serpents among the people, and they bit the people, so that many Israelites died.
04 21:7 The people came to Moses and said, "We have sinned by speaking against the LORD and against you; pray to the LORD to take away the serpents from us." So Moses prayed for the people.
04 21:8 And the LORD said to Moses, "Make a poisonous serpent, and set it on a pole; and everyone who is bitten shall look at it and live."
04 21:9 So Moses made a serpent of bronze, and put it upon a pole; and whenever a serpent bit someone, that person would look at the serpent of bronze and live.
04 21:10 The Israelites set out, and camped in Oboth.
04 21:11 They set out from Oboth, and camped at Iye-abarim, in the wilderness bordering Moab toward the sunrise.
04 21:12 From there they set out, and camped in the Wadi Zered.
04 21:13 From there they set out, and camped on the other side of the Arnon, in the wilderness that extends from the boundary of the Amorites; for the Arnon is the boundary of Moab, between Moab and the Amorites.
04 21:14 Wherefore it is said in the Book of the Wars of the LORD, "Waheb in Suphah and the wadis. The Arnon
04 21:15 and the slopes of the wadis that extend to the seat of Ar, and lie along the border of Moab."
04 21:16 From there they continued to Beer; that is the well of which the LORD said to Moses, "Gather the people together, and I will give them water."
04 21:17 Then Israel sang this song: "Spring up, O well!--Sing to it!--
04 21:18 the well that the leaders sank, that the nobles of the people dug, with the scepter, with the staff." From the wilderness to Mattanah,
04 21:19 from Mattanah to Nahaliel, from Nahaliel to Bamoth,
04 21:20 and from Bamoth to the valley lying in the region of Moab by the top of Pisgah that overlooks the wasteland.
04 21:21 Then Israel sent messengers to King Sihon of the Amorites, saying,
04 21:22 "Let me pass through your land; we will not turn aside into field or vineyard; we will not drink the water of any well; we will go by the King's Highway until we have passed through your territory."
04 21:23 But Sihon would not allow Israel to pass through his territory. Sihon gathered all his people together, and went out against Israel to the wilderness; he came to Jahaz, and fought against Israel.
04 21:24 Israel put him to the sword, and took possession of his land from the Arnon to the Jabbok, as far as to the Ammonites; for the boundary of the Ammonites was strong.
04 21:25 Israel took all these towns, and Israel settled in all the towns of the Amorites, in Heshbon, and in all its villages.
04 21:26 For Heshbon was the city of King Sihon of the Amorites, who had fought against the former king of Moab and captured all his land as far as the Arnon.
04 21:27 Therefore the ballad singers say, "Come to Heshbon, let it be built; let the city of Sihon be established.
04 21:28 For fire came out from Heshbon, flame from the city of Sihon. It devoured Ar of Moab, and swallowed up the heights of the Arnon.
04 21:29 Woe to you, O Moab! You are undone, O people of Chemosh! He has made his sons fugitives, and his daughters captives, to an Amorite king, Sihon.
04 21:30 So their posterity perished from Heshbon to Dibon, and we laid waste until fire spread to Medeba."
04 21:31 Thus Israel settled in the land of the Amorites.
04 21:32 Moses sent to spy out Jazer; and they captured its villages, and dispossessed the Amorites who were there.
04 21:33 Then they turned and went up the road to Bashan; and King Og of Bashan came out against them, he and all his people, to battle at Edrei.
04 21:34 But the LORD said to Moses, "Do not be afraid of him; for I have given him into your hand, with all his people, and all his land. You shall do to him as you did to King Sihon of the Amorites, who ruled in Heshbon."
04 21:35 So they killed him, his sons, and all his people, until there was no survivor left; and they took possession of his land.
04 22:1 The Israelites set out, and camped in the plains of Moab across the Jordan from Jericho.
04 22:2 Now Balak son of Zippor saw all that Israel had done to the Amorites.
04 22:3 Moab was in great dread of the people, because they were so numerous; Moab was overcome with fear of the people of Israel.
04 22:4 And Moab said to the elders of Midian, "This horde will now lick up all that is around us, as an ox licks up the grass of the field." Now Balak son of Zippor was king of Moab at that time.
04 22:5 He sent messengers to Balaam son of Beor at Pethor, which is on the Euphrates, in the land of Amaw, to summon him, saying, "A people has come out of Egypt; they have spread over the face of the earth, and they have settled next to me.
04 22:6 Come now, curse this people for me, since they are stronger than I; perhaps I shall be able to defeat them and drive them from the land; for I know that whomever you bless is blessed, and whomever you curse is cursed."
04 22:7 So the elders of Moab and the elders of Midian departed with the fees for divination in their hand; and they came to Balaam, and gave him Balak's message.
04 22:8 He said to them, "Stay here tonight, and I will bring back word to you, just as the LORD speaks to me"; so the officials of Moab stayed with Balaam.
04 22:9 God came to Balaam and said, "Who are these men with you?"
04 22:10 Balaam said to God, "King Balak son of Zippor of Moab, has sent me this message:
04 22:11 'A people has come out of Egypt and has spread over the face of the earth; now come, curse them for me; perhaps I shall be able to fight against them and drive them out.'"
04 22:12 God said to Balaam, "You shall not go with them; you shall not curse the people, for they are blessed."
04 22:13 So Balaam rose in the morning, and said to the officials of Balak, "Go to your own land, for the LORD has refused to let me go with you."
04 22:14 So the officials of Moab rose and went to Balak, and said, "Balaam refuses to come with us."
04 22:15 Once again Balak sent officials, more numerous and more distinguished than these.
04 22:16 They came to Balaam and said to him, "Thus says Balak son of Zippor: 'Do not let anything hinder you from coming to me;
04 22:17 for I will surely do you great honor, and whatever you say to me I will do; come, curse this people for me.'"
04 22:18 But Balaam replied to the servants of Balak, "Although Balak were to give me his house full of silver and gold, I could not go beyond the command of the LORD my God, to do less or more.
04 22:19 You remain here, as the others did, so that I may learn what more the LORD may say to me."
04 22:20 That night God came to Balaam and said to him, "If the men have come to summon you, get up and go with them; but do only what I tell you to do."
04 22:21 So Balaam got up in the morning, saddled his donkey, and went with the officials of Moab.
04 22:22 God's anger was kindled because he was going, and the angel of the LORD took his stand in the road as his adversary. Now he was riding on the donkey, and his two servants were with him.
04 22:23 The donkey saw the angel of the LORD standing in the road, with a drawn sword in his hand; so the donkey turned off the road, and went into the field; and Balaam struck the donkey, to turn it back onto the road.
04 22:24 Then the angel of the LORD stood in a narrow path between the vineyards, with a wall on either side.
04 22:25 When the donkey saw the angel of the LORD, it scraped against the wall, and scraped Balaam's foot against the wall; so he struck it again.
04 22:26 Then the angel of the LORD went ahead, and stood in a narrow place, where there was no way to turn either to the right or to the left.
04 22:27 When the donkey saw the angel of the LORD, it lay down under Balaam; and Balaam's anger was kindled, and he struck the donkey with his staff.
04 22:28 Then the LORD opened the mouth of the donkey, and it said to Balaam, "What have I done to you, that you have struck me these three times?"
04 22:29 Balaam said to the donkey, "Because you have made a fool of me! I wish I had a sword in my hand! I would kill you right now!"
04 22:30 But the donkey said to Balaam, "Am I not your donkey, which you have ridden all your life to this day? Have I been in the habit of treating you this way?" And he said, "No."
04 22:31 Then the LORD opened the eyes of Balaam, and he saw the angel of the LORD standing in the road, with his drawn sword in his hand; and he bowed down, falling on his face.
04 22:32 The angel of the LORD said to him, "Why have you struck your donkey these three times? I have come out as an adversary, because your way is perverse before me.
04 22:33 The donkey saw me, and turned away from me these three times. If it had not turned away from me, surely just now I would have killed you and let it live."
04 22:34 Then Balaam said to the angel of the LORD, "I have sinned, for I did not know that you were standing in the road to oppose me. Now therefore, if it is displeasing to you, I will return home."
04 22:35 The angel of the LORD said to Balaam, "Go with the men; but speak only what I tell you to speak." So Balaam went on with the officials of Balak.
04 22:36 When Balak heard that Balaam had come, he went out to meet him at Ir-moab, on the boundary formed by the Arnon, at the farthest point of the boundary.
04 22:37 Balak said to Balaam, "Did I not send to summon you? Why did you not come to me? Am I not able to honor you?"
04 22:38 Balaam said to Balak, "I have come to you now, but do I have power to say just anything? The word God puts in my mouth, that is what I must say."
04 22:39 Then Balaam went with Balak, and they came to Kiriath-huzoth.
04 22:40 Balak sacrificed oxen and sheep, and sent them to Balaam and to the officials who were with him.
04 22:41 On the next day Balak took Balaam and brought him up to Bamoth-baal; and from there he could see part of the people of Israel.
04 23:1 Then Balaam said to Balak, "Build me seven altars here, and prepare seven bulls and seven rams for me."
04 23:2 Balak did as Balaam had said; and Balak and Balaam offered a bull and a ram on each altar.
04 23:3 Then Balaam said to Balak, "Stay here beside your burnt offerings while I go aside. Perhaps the LORD will come to meet me. Whatever he shows me I will tell you." And he went to a bare height.
04 23:4 Then God met Balaam; and Balaam said to him, "I have arranged the seven altars, and have offered a bull and a ram on each altar."
04 23:5 The LORD put a word in Balaam's mouth, and said, "Return to Balak, and this is what you must say."
04 23:6 So he returned to Balak, who was standing beside his burnt offerings with all the officials of Moab.
04 23:7 Then Balaam uttered his oracle, saying: "Balak has brought me from Aram, the king of Moab from the eastern mountains: 'Come, curse Jacob for me; Come, denounce Israel!'
04 23:8 How can I curse whom God has not cursed? How can I denounce those whom the LORD has not denounced?
04 23:9 For from the top of the crags I see him, from the hills I behold him; Here is a people living alone, and not reckoning itself among the nations!
04 23:10 Who can count the dust of Jacob, or number the dust-cloud of Israel? Let me die the death of the upright, and let my end be like his!"
04 23:11 Then Balak said to Balaam, "What have you done to me? I brought you to curse my enemies, but now you have done nothing but bless them."
04 23:12 He answered, "Must I not take care to say what the LORD puts into my mouth?"
04 23:13 So Balak said to him, "Come with me to another place from which you may see them; you shall see only part of them, and shall not see them all; then curse them for me from there."
04 23:14 So he took him to the field of Zophim, to the top of Pisgah. He built seven altars, and offered a bull and a ram on each altar.
04 23:15 Balaam said to Balak, "Stand here beside your burnt offerings, while I meet the LORD over there.
04 23:16 The LORD met Balaam, put a word into his mouth, and said, "Return to Balak, and this is what you shall say."
04 23:17 When he came to him, he was standing beside his burnt offerings with the officials of Moab. Balak said to him, "What has the LORD said?"
04 23:18 Then Balaam uttered his oracle, saying: "Rise, Balak, and hear; listen to me, O son of Zippor:
04 23:19 God is not a human being, that he should lie, or a mortal, that he should change his mind. Has he promised, and will he not do it? Has he spoken, and will he not fulfill it?
04 23:20 See, I received a command to bless; he has blessed, and I cannot revoke it.
04 23:21 He has not beheld misfortune in Jacob; nor has he seen trouble in Israel. The LORD their God is with them, acclaimed as a king among them.
04 23:22 God, who brings them out of Egypt, is like the horns of a wild ox for them.
04 23:23 Surely there is no enchantment against Jacob, no divination against Israel; now it shall be said of Jacob and Israel, 'See what God has done!'
04 23:24 Look, a people rising up like a lioness, and rousing itself like a lion! It does not lie down until it has eaten the prey and drunk the blood of the slain."
04 23:25 Then Balak said to Balaam, "Do not curse them at all, and do not bless them at all."
04 23:26 But Balaam answered Balak, "Did I not tell you, 'Whatever the LORD says, that is what I must do'?"
04 23:27 So Balak said to Balaam, "Come now, I will take you to another place; perhaps it will please God that you may curse them for me from there."
04 23:28 So Balak took Balaam to the top of Peor, which overlooks the wasteland.
04 23:29 Balaam said to Balak, "Build me seven altars here, and prepare seven bulls and seven rams for me."
04 23:30 So Balak did as Balaam had said, and offered a bull and a ram on each altar.
04 24:1 Now Balaam saw that it pleased the LORD to bless Israel, so he did not go, as at other times, to look for omens, but set his face toward the wilderness.
04 24:2 Balaam looked up and saw Israel camping tribe by tribe. Then the spirit of God came upon him,
04 24:3 and he uttered his oracle, saying: "The oracle of Balaam son of Beor, the oracle of the man whose eye is clear,
04 24:4 the oracle of one who hears the words of God, who sees the vision of the Almighty, who falls down, but with eyes uncovered:
04 24:5 how fair are your tents, O Jacob, your encampments, O Israel!
04 24:6 Like palm-groves that stretch far away, like gardens beside a river, like aloes that the LORD has planted, like cedar trees beside the waters.
04 24:7 Water shall flow from his buckets, and his seed shall have abundant water, his king shall be higher than Agag, and his kingdom shall be exalted.
04 24:8 God who brings him out of Egypt, is like the horns of a wild ox for him; he shall devour the nations that are his foes and break their bones. He shall strike with his arrows.
04 24:9 He crouched, he lay down like a lion, and like a lioness; who will rouse him up? Blessed is everyone who blesses you, and cursed is everyone who curses you."
04 24:10 Then Balak's anger was kindled against Balaam, and he struck his hands together. Balak said to Balaam, "I summoned you to curse my enemies, but instead you have blessed them these three times.
04 24:11 Now be off with you! Go home! I said, 'I will reward you richly,' but the LORD has denied you any reward."
04 24:12 And Balaam said to Balak, "Did I not tell your messengers whom you sent to me,
04 24:13 'If Balak should give me his house full of silver and gold, I would not be able to go beyond the word of the LORD, to do either good or bad of my own will; what the LORD says, that is what I will say'?
04 24:14 So now, I am going to my people; let me advise you what this people will do to your people in days to come."
04 24:15 So he uttered his oracle, saying: "The oracle of Balaam son of Beor, the oracle of the man whose eye is clear,
04 24:16 the oracle of one who hears the words of God, and knows the knowledge of the Most High, who sees the vision of the Almighty, who falls down, but with his eyes uncovered:
04 24:17 I see him, but not now; I behold him, but not near--a star shall come out of Jacob, and a scepter shall rise out of Israel; it shall crush the borderlands of Moab, and the territory of all the Shethites.
04 24:18 Edom will become a possession, Seir a possession of its enemies, while Israel does valiantly.
04 24:19 One out of Jacob shall rule, and destroy the survivors of Ir."
04 24:20 Then he looked on Amalek, and uttered his oracle, saying: "First among the nations was Amalek, but its end is to perish forever."
04 24:21 Then he looked on the Kenite, and uttered his oracle, saying: "Enduring is your dwelling place, and your nest is set in the rock;
04 24:22 yet Kain is destined for burning. How long shall Asshur take you away captive?"
04 24:23 Again he uttered his oracle, saying: "Alas, who shall live when God does this?
04 24:24 But ships shall come from Kittim and shall afflict Asshur and Eber; and he also shall perish forever."
04 24:25 Then Balaam got up and went back to his place, and Balak also went his way.
04 25:1 While Israel was staying at Shittim, the people began to have sexual relations with the women of Moab.
04 25:2 These invited the people to the sacrifices of their gods, and the people ate and bowed down to their gods.
04 25:3 Thus Israel yoked itself to the Baal of Peor, and the LORD's anger was kindled against Israel.
04 25:4 The LORD said to Moses, "Take all the chiefs of the people, and impale them in the sun before the LORD, in order that the fierce anger of the LORD may turn away from Israel."
04 25:5 And Moses said to the judges of Israel, "Each of you shall kill any of your people who have yoked themselves to the Baal of Peor."
04 25:6 Just then one of the Israelites came and brought a Midianite woman into his family, in the sight of Moses and in the sight of the whole congregation of the Israelites, while they were weeping at the entrance of the tent of meeting.
04 25:7 When Phinehas son of Eleazar, son of Aaron the priest, saw it, he got up and left the congregation. Taking a spear in his hand,
04 25:8 he went after the Israelite man into the tent, and pierced the two of them, the Israelite and the woman, through the belly. So the plague was stopped among the people of Israel.
04 25:9 Nevertheless those that died by the plague were twenty-four thousand.
04 25:10 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 25:11 "Phinehas son of Eleazar, son of Aaron the priest, has turned back my wrath from the Israelites by manifesting such zeal among them on my behalf that in my jealousy I did not consume the Israelites.
04 25:12 Therefore say, 'I hereby grant him my covenant of peace.
04 25:13 It shall be for him and for his descendants after him a covenant of perpetual priesthood, because he was zealous for his God, and made atonement for the Israelites.'"
04 25:14 The name of the slain Israelite man, who was killed with the Midianite woman, was Zimri son of Salu, head of an ancestral house belonging to the Simeonites.
04 25:15 The name of the Midianite woman who was killed was Cozbi daughter of Zur, who was the head of a clan, an ancestral house in Midian.
04 25:16 The LORD said to Moses,
04 25:17 "Harass the Midianites, and defeat them;
04 25:18 for they have harassed you by the trickery with which they deceived you in the affair of Peor, and in the affair of Cozbi, the daughter of a leader of Midian, their sister; she was killed on the day of the plague that resulted from Peor."
04 26:1 After the plague the LORD said to Moses and to Eleazar son of Aaron the priest,
04 26:2 "Take a census of the whole congregation of the Israelites, from twenty years old and upward, by their ancestral houses, everyone in Israel able to go to war."
04 26:3 Moses and Eleazar the priest spoke with them in the plains of Moab by the Jordan opposite Jericho, saying,
04 26:4 "Take a census of the people, from twenty years old and upward," as the LORD commanded Moses. The Israelites, who came out of the land of Egypt, were:
04 26:5 Reuben, the firstborn of Israel. The descendants of Reuben: of Hanoch, the clan of the Hanochites; of Pallu, the clan of the Palluites;
04 26:6 of Hezron, the clan of the Hezronites; of Carmi, the clan of the Carmites.
04 26:7 These are the clans of the Reubenites; the number of those enrolled was forty-three thousand seven hundred thirty.
04 26:8 And the descendants of Pallu: Eliab.
04 26:9 The descendants of Eliab: Nemuel, Dathan, and Abiram. These are the same Dathan and Abiram, chosen from the congregation, who rebelled against Moses and Aaron in the company of Korah, when they rebelled against the LORD,
04 26:10 and the earth opened its mouth and swallowed them up along with Korah, when that company died, when the fire devoured two hundred fifty men; and they became a warning.
04 26:11 Notwithstanding, the sons of Korah did not die.
04 26:12 The descendants of Simeon by their clans: of Nemuel, the clan of the Nemuelites; of Jamin, the clan of the Jaminites; of Jachin, the clan of the Jachinites;
04 26:13 of Zerah, the clan of the Zerahites; of Shaul, the clan of the Shaulites.
04 26:14 These are the clans of the Simeonites, twenty-two thousand two hundred.
04 26:15 The children of Gad by their clans: of Zephon, the clan of the Zephonites; of Haggi, the clan of the Haggites; of Shuni, the clan of the Shunites;
04 26:16 of Ozni, the clan of the Oznites; of Eri, the clan of the Erites;
04 26:17 of Arod, the clan of the Arodites; of Areli, the clan of the Arelites.
04 26:18 These are the clans of the Gadites: the number of those enrolled was forty thousand five hundred.
04 26:19 The sons of Judah: Er and Onan; Er and Onan died in the land of Canaan.
04 26:20 The descendants of Judah by their clans were: of Shelah, the clan of the Shelanites; of Perez, the clan of the Perezites; of Zerah, the clan of the Zerahites.
04 26:21 The descendants of Perez were: of Hezron, the clan of the Hezronites; of Hamul, the clan of the Hamulites.
04 26:22 These are the clans of Judah: the number of those enrolled was seventy-six thousand five hundred.
04 26:23 The descendants of Issachar by their clans: of Tola, the clan of the Tolaites; of Puvah, the clan of the Punites;
04 26:24 of Jashub, the clan of the Jashubites; of Shimron, the clan of the Shimronites.
04 26:25 These are the clans of Issachar: sixty-four thousand three hundred enrolled.
04 26:26 The descendants of Zebulun by their clans: of Sered, the clan of the Seredites; of Elon, the clan of the Elonites; of Jahleel, the clan of the Jahleelites.
04 26:27 These are the clans of the Zebulunites; the number of those enrolled was sixty thousand five hundred.
04 26:28 The sons of Joseph by their clans: Manasseh and Ephraim.
04 26:29 The descendants of Manasseh: of Machir, the clan of the Machirites; and Machir was the father of Gilead; of Gilead, the clan of the Gileadites.
04 26:30 These are the descendants of Gilead: of Iezer, the clan of the Iezerites; of Helek, the clan of the Helekites;
04 26:31 and of Asriel, the clan of the Asrielites; and of Shechem, the clan of the Shechemites;
04 26:32 and of Shemida, the clan of the Shemidaites; and of Hepher, the clan of the Hepherites.
04 26:33 Now Zelophehad son of Hepher had no sons, but daughters: and the names of the daughters of Zelophehad were Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.
04 26:34 These are the clans of Manasseh; the number of those enrolled was fifty-two thousand seven hundred.
04 26:35 These are the descendants of Ephraim according to their clans: of Shuthelah, the clan of the Shuthelahites; of Becher, the clan of the Becherites; of Tahan, the clan of the Tahanites.
04 26:36 And these are the descendants of Shuthelah: of Eran, the clan of the Eranites.
04 26:37 These are the clans of the Ephraimites: the number of those enrolled was thirty-two thousand five hundred. These are the descendants of Joseph by their clans.
04 26:38 The descendants of Benjamin by their clans: of Bela, the clan of the Belaites; of Ashbel, the clan of the Ashbelites; of Ahiram, the clan of the Ahiramites;
04 26:39 of Shephupham, the clan of the Shuphamites; of Hupham, the clan of the Huphamites.
04 26:40 And the sons of Bela were Ard and Naaman: of Ard, the clan of the Ardites; of Naaman, the clan of the Naamites.
04 26:41 These are the descendants of Benjamin by their clans; the number of those enrolled was forty-five thousand six hundred.
04 26:42 These are the descendants of Dan by their clans: of Shuham, the clan of the Shuhamites. These are the clans of Dan by their clans.
04 26:43 All the clans of the Shuhamites: sixty-four thousand four hundred enrolled.
04 26:44 The descendants of Asher by their families: of Imnah, the clan of the Imnites; of Ishvi, the clan of the Ishvites; of Beriah, the clan of the Beriites.
04 26:45 Of the descendants of Beriah: of Heber, the clan of the Heberites; of Malchiel, the clan of the Malchielites.
04 26:46 And the name of the daughter of Asher was Serah.
04 26:47 These are the clans of the Asherites: the number of those enrolled was fifty-three thousand four hundred.
04 26:48 The descendants of Naphtali by their clans: of Jahzeel, the clan of the Jahzeelites; of Guni, the clan of the Gunites;
04 26:49 of Jezer, the clan of the Jezerites; of Shillem, the clan of the Shillemites.
04 26:50 These are the Naphtalites by their clans: the number of those enrolled was forty-five thousand four hundred.
04 26:51 This was the number of the Israelites enrolled: six hundred and one thousand seven hundred thirty.
04 26:52 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 26:53 To these the land shall be apportioned for inheritance according to the number of names.
04 26:54 To a large tribe you shall give a large inheritance, and to a small tribe you shall give a small inheritance; every tribe shall be given its inheritance according to its enrollment.
04 26:55 But the land shall be apportioned by lot; according to the names of their ancestral tribes they shall inherit.
04 26:56 Their inheritance shall be apportioned according to lot between the larger and the smaller.
04 26:57 This is the enrollment of the Levites by their clans: of Gershon, the clan of the Gershonites; of Kohath, the clan of the Kohathites; of Merari, the clan of the Merarites.
04 26:58 These are the clans of Levi: the clan of the Libnites, the clan of the Hebronites, the clan of the Mahlites, the clan of the Mushites, the clan of the Korahites. Now Kohath was the father of Amram.
04 26:59 The name of Amram's wife was Jochebed daughter of Levi, who was born to Levi in Egypt; and she bore to Amram: Aaron, Moses, and their sister Miriam.
04 26:60 To Aaron were born Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.
04 26:61 But Nadab and Abihu died when they offered illicit fire before the LORD.
04 26:62 The number of those enrolled was twenty-three thousand, every male one month old and up; for they were not enrolled among the Israelites because there was no allotment given to them among the Israelites.
04 26:63 These were those enrolled by Moses and Eleazar the priest, who enrolled the Israelites in the plains of Moab by the Jordan opposite Jericho.
04 26:64 Among these there was not one of those enrolled by Moses and Aaron the priest, who had enrolled the Israelites in the wilderness of Sinai.
04 26:65 For the LORD had said of them, "They shall die in the wilderness." Not one of them was left, except Caleb son of Jephunneh and Joshua son of Nun.
04 27:1 Then the daughters of Zelophehad came forward. Zelophehad was son of Hepher son of Gilead son of Machir son of Manasseh son of Joseph, a member of the Manassite clans. The names of his daughters were: Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.
04 27:2 They stood before Moses, Eleazar the priest, the leaders, and all the congregation, at the entrance of the tent of meeting, and they said,
04 27:3 "Our father died in the wilderness; he was not among the company of those who gathered themselves together against the LORD in the company of Korah, but died for his own sin; and he had no sons.
04 27:4 Why should the name of our father be taken away from his clan because he had no son? Give to us a possession among our father's brothers."
04 27:5 Moses brought their case before the LORD.
04 27:6 And the LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 27:7 The daughters of Zelophehad are right in what they are saying; you shall indeed let them possess an inheritance among their father's brothers and pass the inheritance of their father on to them.
04 27:8 You shall also say to the Israelites, "If a man dies, and has no son, then you shall pass his inheritance on to his daughter.
04 27:9 If he has no daughter, then you shall give his inheritance to his brothers.
04 27:10 If he has no brothers, then you shall give his inheritance to his father's brothers.
04 27:11 And if his father has no brothers, then you shall give his inheritance to the nearest kinsman of his clan, and he shall possess it. It shall be for the Israelites a statute and ordinance, as the LORD commanded Moses."
04 27:12 The LORD said to Moses, "Go up this mountain of the Abarim range, and see the land that I have given to the Israelites.
04 27:13 When you have seen it, you also shall be gathered to your people, as your brother Aaron was,
04 27:14 because you rebelled against my word in the wilderness of Zin when the congregation quarreled with me. You did not show my holiness before their eyes at the waters." (These are the waters of Meribah of Kadesh in the wilderness of Zin.)
04 27:15 Moses spoke to the LORD, saying,
04 27:16 "Let the LORD, the God of the spirits of all flesh, appoint someone over the congregation
04 27:17 who shall go out before them and come in before them, who shall lead them out and bring them in, so that the congregation of the LORD may not be like sheep without a shepherd."
04 27:18 So the LORD said to Moses, "Take Joshua son of Nun, a man in whom is the spirit, and lay your hand upon him;
04 27:19 have him stand before Eleazar the priest and all the congregation, and commission him in their sight.
04 27:20 You shall give him some of your authority, so that all the congregation of the Israelites may obey.
04 27:21 But he shall stand before Eleazar the priest, who shall inquire for him by the decision of the Urim before the LORD; at his word they shall go out, and at his word they shall come in, both he and all the Israelites with him, the whole congregation."
04 27:22 So Moses did as the LORD commanded him. He took Joshua and had him stand before Eleazar the priest and the whole congregation;
04 27:23 he laid his hands on him and commissioned him--as the LORD had directed through Moses.
04 28:1 The LORD spoke to Moses, saying:
04 28:2 Command the Israelites, and say to them: My offering, the food for my offerings by fire, my pleasing odor, you shall take care to offer to me at its appointed time.
04 28:3 And you shall say to them, This is the offering by fire that you shall offer to the LORD: two male lambs a year old without blemish, daily, as a regular offering.
04 28:4 One lamb you shall offer in the morning, and the other lamb you shall offer at twilight
04 28:5 also one-tenth of an ephah of choice flour for a grain offering, mixed with one-fourth of a hin of beaten oil.
04 28:6 It is a regular burnt offering, ordained at Mount Sinai for a pleasing odor, an offering by fire to the LORD.
04 28:7 Its drink offering shall be one-fourth of a hin for each lamb; in the sanctuary you shall pour out a drink offering of strong drink to the LORD.
04 28:8 The other lamb you shall offer at twilight with a grain offering and a drink offering like the one in the morning; you shall offer it as an offering by fire, a pleasing odor to the LORD.
04 28:9 On the sabbath day: two male lambs a year old without blemish, and two-tenths of an ephah of choice flour for a grain offering, mixed with oil, and its drink offering--
04 28:10 this is the burnt offering for every sabbath, in addition to the regular burnt offering and its drink offering.
04 28:11 At the beginnings of your months you shall offer a burnt offering to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, seven male lambs a year old without blemish;
04 28:12 also three-tenths of an ephah of choice flour for a grain offering, mixed with oil, for each bull; and two-tenths of choice flour for a grain offering, mixed with oil, for the one ram;
04 28:13 and one-tenth of choice flour mixed with oil as a grain offering for every lamb--a burnt offering of pleasing odor, an offering by fire to the LORD.
04 28:14 Their drink offerings shall be half a hin of wine for a bull, one-third of a hin for a ram, and one-fourth of a hin for a lamb. This is the burnt offering of every month throughout the months of the year.
04 28:15 And there shall be one male goat for a sin offering to the LORD; it shall be offered in addition to the regular burnt offering and its drink offering.
04 28:16 On the fourteenth day of the first month there shall be a passover offering to the LORD.
04 28:17 And on the fifteenth day of this month is a festival; seven days shall unleavened bread be eaten.
04 28:18 On the first day there shall be a holy convocation. You shall not work at your occupations.
04 28:19 You shall offer an offering by fire, a burnt offering to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, and seven male lambs a year old; see that they are without blemish.
04 28:20 Their grain offering shall be of choice flour mixed with oil: three-tenths of an ephah shall you offer for a bull, and two-tenths for a ram;
04 28:21 one-tenth shall you offer for each of the seven lambs;
04 28:22 also one male goat for a sin offering, to make atonement for you.
04 28:23 You shall offer these in addition to the burnt offering of the morning, which belongs to the regular burnt offering.
04 28:24 In the same way you shall offer daily, for seven days, the food of an offering by fire, a pleasing odor to the LORD; it shall be offered in addition to the regular burnt offering and its drink offering.
04 28:25 And on the seventh day you shall have a holy convocation; you shall not work at your occupations.
04 28:26 On the day of the first fruits, when you offer a grain offering of new grain to the LORD at your festival of weeks, you shall have a holy convocation; you shall not work at your occupations.
04 28:27 You shall offer a burnt offering, a pleasing odor to the LORD: two young bulls, one ram, seven male lambs a year old.
04 28:28 Their grain offering shall be of choice flour mixed with oil, three-tenths of an ephah for each bull, two-tenths for one ram,
04 28:29 one-tenth for each of the seven lambs;
04 28:30 with one male goat, to make atonement for you.
04 28:31 In addition to the regular burnt offering with its grain offering, you shall offer them and their drink offering. They shall be without blemish.
04 29:1 On the first day of the seventh month you shall have a holy convocation; you shall not work at your occupations. It is a day for you to blow the trumpets,
04 29:2 and you shall offer a burnt offering, a pleasing odor to the LORD: one young bull, one ram, seven male lambs a year old without blemish.
04 29:3 Their grain offering shall be of choice flour mixed with oil, three-tenths of one ephah for the bull, two-tenths for the ram,
04 29:4 and one-tenth for each of the seven lambs;
04 29:5 with one male goat for a sin offering, to make atonement for you.
04 29:6 These are in addition to the burnt offering of the new moon and its grain offering, and the regular burnt offering and its grain offering, and their drink offerings, according to the ordinance for them, a pleasing odor, an offering by fire to the LORD.
04 29:7 On the tenth day of this seventh month you shall have a holy convocation, and deny yourselves; you shall do no work.
04 29:8 You shall offer a burnt offering to the LORD, a pleasing odor: one young bull, one ram, seven male lambs a year old. They shall be without blemish.
04 29:9 Their grain offering shall be of choice flour mixed with oil, three-tenths of an ephah for the bull, two-tenths for the one ram,
04 29:10 one-tenth for each of the seven lambs;
04 29:11 with one male goat for a sin offering, in addition to the sin offering of atonement, and the regular burnt offering and its grain offering, and their drink offerings.
